info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued September 30 at 3:53AM EDT until October 01 at 10:00AM EDT by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EDT SUNDAY... ...COASTAL FLOOD STATEMENT IS CANCELLED... * WHAT...Saltwater flooding with little relief during times of low tide. * WHERE...Upper Florida Keys. * WHEN...Through Sunday morning. * IMPACTS...Saltwater flooding of low elevation streets and lots is expected. Some storm drains will overflow, and some seawalls and docks will be overtopped. Boaters can expect less clearance under fixed bridges. Motorists should remember that persistent puddles around the times of high tide are almost certain to contain a mix of saltwater.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
